==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stephanotis
<hw>Steph`a*no"tis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ fit for a crown, fr. <?/ crown.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of climbing asclepiadaceous shrubs, of
Madagascar, Malaya, etc. They have fleshy or coriaceous opposite leaves,
and large white waxy flowers in cymes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A perfume said to be prepared from the flowers of
<spn>Stephanotis floribunda</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stepladder</ent>⟦br⟧
